OL,3,CFamily pay tribute to 'loving, funny'
OL,4,Cteen who died after being struck by car
OL,6,F"Ethan's legacy will continue to shine
OL,7,Fthrough in life with the donation of
OL,8,Fhis organs to save another life. We
OL,9,Fare truly proud of him as much in life
OL,10,Fas in death. May he rest in peace, and
OL,11,Fwe ask to grieve in private".
OL,13,FThe sport for all centre in Oldham,
OL,14,Fwhere Ethan played and coached, said:
OL,15,F"In light of this immense loss, we
OL,16,Fwill be observing a minute of silence
OL,17,Fbefore each game on Saturday as a
OL,18,Fgesture of respect and remembrance. We
OL,19,Fkindly ask all teams to gather on the
OL,20,Fcourt prior to their fixtures for this
OL,21,Fsolemn moment.
